Name of Tester: Sunita Kore
Source files to be added to the .pjt file Must include path from 'Source Code Directory' setting on the Unit Test Tool Options dialog Include Files:

Code File(s) Under Test: Sa_MtrVel.c



Code File(s) Version: 5



Module Design Document: MotorVelocity_MDD.doc



Module Design Document Version: 6



Data Dictionary Version: 3



Unit Test Plan Version: 2



Optimization Level: Level 2



Compiler (CodeGen) Version: TMS470_4.9.5



Model Type: Excel Macro



Model Version: Nexteer EPS Unit Test Tool 2.7d/EPS Library 1.31



Total FLASH Used (Bytes): 1394



Total RAM Used (Bytes): 42



Total CALS Used (Bytes): 54



Special Test Requirements:




Test Date: 12/26/2014



Comments: Note1: Inline functions defined in "Globalmacro.h" are not unit tested.
Note2: In function "MtrVel_Per1", the values of variable "MechMtrPos2Timestamp_USec_u32" and "MtrVel_PrevMtrPosSampleTime2_uS_M_u32" are taken slightly different from the actual range, to get value of "DeltaTime2_uS_T_f32" in the range of "1800 - 2200" as per the guidelines mentioned in MDD.
Note3: In function "CalcCoarseVel", the return value is going beyond given range and it's accepted because it is later limited to +/- 1350.
Note4: In function "RegressionFit" , the path 'P5' i.e. "(SumDeltaSqT_uSsq_T_f32 > FLT_EPSILON) = FALSE" has been covered by not following the specific guidelines mentioned in the MDD(to calculate values of variable "MtrVel3_TimeBuffer_uS_M_u16p0[4][8]") and have been given value as '0' for all array elements.
Note5: "CBD_Sandbox_dbg.map" is embedded for reference.

Sheet 25: Clarifications
Program Developer Issue 1 Response 1 Issue 2 Response 2 Issue 3 Response 3
EA3.x Selva In function "MtrVel_Per1", the values of variable "MechMtrPos2Timestamp_USec_u32" and "MtrVel_PrevMtrPosSampleTime2_uS_M_u32" are taken slightly different from the actual range, to get value of "DeltaTime2_uS_T_f32" in the range of "1800 - 2200" as per the guidelines mentioned in MDD. confirmation given by developer for previous source version. In function "CalcCoarseVel", the return value is going beyond given range and it's accepted because it is later limited to +/- 1350. confirmation given by developer for previous source version. In function "RegressionFit" , the path 'P5' i.e. "(SumDeltaSqT_uSsq_T_f32 > FLT_EPSILON) = FALSE" has been covered by not following the specific guidelines mentioned in the MDD(to calculate values of variable "MtrVel3_TimeBuffer_uS_M_u16p0[4][8]") and have been given value as '0' for all array elements. confirmation given by developer for previous source version.
